<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta
      name="viewport"
      content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"
    />
    <title>Terms of Use | OnTask Logistics LLC</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Terms of Use for the OnTask Logistics LLC website, describing acceptable use, service limitations, and important notices for visitors."
    />
    <style>
      :root {
        --navy: #0b1530;
        --text-main: #111827;
        --text-muted: #4b5563;
        --bg-body: #f9fafb;
        --border-subtle: #e1e5f0;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }

      body {
        font-family: "Inter", system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,
          "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
        background: var(--bg-body);
        color: var(--text-main);
        line-height: 1.7;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      }

      main {
        min-height: 100vh;
      }

      .shell {
        max-width: 760px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 64px 20px 96px;
      }

      .page-title {
        font-size: 1.6rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        color: var(--navy);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }

      .page-intro {
        font-size: 0.94rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        margin-bottom: 28px;
        max-width: 40rem;
      }

      .section {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
        padding-top: 20px;
        margin-top: 20px;
      }

      .section:first-of-type {
        border-top: none;
        padding-top: 0;
        margin-top: 0;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 0.98rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--navy);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }

      .section-body {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
      }

      .section-body p + p {
        margin-top: 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        margin-top: 32px;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
        text-underline-offset: 2px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <div class="shell">
        <h1 class="page-title">Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="page-intro">
          These Terms of Use apply to your access to and use of the OnTask
          Logistics LLC website. By using this site, you acknowledge that you
          have read and understood the information below.
        </p>

        <section class="section" aria-labelledby="informational-purpose">
          <h2 id="informational-purpose" class="section-title">
            Website informational purpose
          </h2>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              This website is intended to provide high-level information about
              OnTask Logistics LLC and the courier services it may offer.
              Content on this site, including descriptions of routes, coverage
              areas, and operational standards, is for informational purposes
              only and does not constitute a binding service proposal or
              guarantee.
            </p>
            <p>
              Any decisions regarding courier services, route structure, or
              engagement terms are made separately, based on a detailed review
              of your needs and a confirmed service agreement.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" aria-labelledby="no-service-agreement">
          <h2 id="no-service-agreement" class="section-title">
            Consultation requests and service agreements
          </h2>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              Submitting a route consultation form or contacting OnTask
              Logistics LLC through this website does not create a service
              agreement, contract, or obligation to provide courier services.
            </p>
            <p>
              Any service engagement must be separately reviewed and agreed in
              writing or through another documented acceptance process. OnTask
              Logistics LLC reserves the right to decline requests that do not
              align with operational capacity, coverage areas, or route
              structure.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" aria-labelledby="coverage-availability">
          <h2 id="coverage-availability" class="section-title">
            Services, coverage, and scheduling availability
          </h2>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              All services described on this site are subject to route coverage,
              scheduling availability, and operational fit. Coverage areas may
              change over time as routes are adjusted, expanded, or retired.
            </p>
            <p>
              Any indication that a county, city, or region is served should be
              understood as general guidance. Actual service availability
              depends on factors such as existing and planned routes, pickup
              timing, volume, and operational constraints.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" aria-labelledby="liability">
          <h2 id="liability" class="section-title">
            Limitation of liability for website errors or downtime
          </h2>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              OnTask Logistics LLC makes reasonable efforts to keep this website
              accurate and available. However, the site may occasionally contain
              errors, omissions, or technical issues, and it may be temporarily
              unavailable due to maintenance or factors outside OnTask's
              control.
            </p>
            <p>
              To the fullest extent permitted by law, OnTask Logistics LLC is
              not liable for any loss, interruption, or damages arising from:
              (a) use or inability to use the website; (b) reliance on website
              content that is outdated or incorrect; or (c) any errors,
              omissions, or technical problems affecting access to the site.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" aria-labelledby="content-changes">
          <h2 id="content-changes" class="section-title">
            Changes and updates to website content
          </h2>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              Information on this website, including descriptions of services,
              coverage areas, example routes, and policies, may be updated or
              changed at any time without prior notice. Updated content applies
              from the time it is published on the site.
            </p>
            <p>
              If you are considering a service engagement, you should not rely
              solely on previously viewed content. Instead, you should confirm
              current terms, coverage, and availability directly with OnTask
              Logistics LLC as part of the consultation and onboarding process.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <p class="footer-note">
          If you have questions about these Terms of Use, you can contact
          OnTask Logistics LLC at
          <a href="mailto:info@ontask-logistics.com"
            >info@ontask-logistics.com</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

